modules.description: Handles cryptographic key exchange, data encryption, and endpoint authentication using TLS protocols. Operates on byte sequences, X.509 certificates, and cryptographic keys to establish secure communication channels. Enables secure web transactions, encrypted email exchanges, and protected data transfer over untrusted networks.

Reads PEM-encoded certificates and private keys from files or directories, constructs certificate chains, and builds X.509 authenticators using CA files, directories, or fingerprint-based validation. Processes PEM data into lists of X.509 certificates and combines private keys with certificate chains. Supports hash-specific validation and CRL loading for secure authentication workflows.

Establishes TLS sessions over network flows, handling server and client handshakes with configured certificates and host validation. Supports session renegotiation with custom authenticators and certificate validation, and key updates for TLS 1.3. Operates on Eio flow resources, providing session epoch data for active connections.
